 Police shoot, kill armed man holding 17-month-old hostage in North Middletown (Credit: Karla Bardinas - News 12 New Jersey)

Police shot and killed a man who was armed with a knife and holding a 17-month-old boy hostage in North Middletown, the state Attorney Generalas Office confirmed.

Officials say a preliminary investigation shows the Monmouth County SWAT team entered the home and fatally shot the suspect after negotiations failed.

The 17-month-old boy was unharmed in the incident. No police were injured.

